n' \\\\\\\"\\\"'$f\\\"; rg -n '\\\"'isInstanceOf\\\\\\\\(|assertThat\\\\\\\\(deserialized\\\\\\\\)|return new .*PrivateKey|return new .*PublicKey|keyPair\\\\\\\\.getPrivate|keyPair\\\\\\\\.getPublic' \\\\\\\"\\\"'$f\\\"; done'\",\"aggregated_output\":\"FILE tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImplTest.java\\nFILE tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/X509UtilTest.java\\n63:        assertThat(spi).isInstanceOf(X509StoreCertCollection.class);\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_35\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’ve identified a cluster of BouncyCastle key tests that all exercise Java serialization and currently have no metadata coverage at all. Instead of adding one entry at a time for obviously related classes, I’m patching the metadata file with the exact key types under test and conditioning each entry on that same type being reached.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_36\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImplTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_36\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImplTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\\nimport java.math.BigInteger;\\nimport java.util.Enumeration;\\n\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Integer;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1ObjectIdentifier;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.util.PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImplTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void writesAndReadsEmptyBagAttributeState() throws Exception {\\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl original = new PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl();\\n\\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl restored = readCarrier(writeCarrier(original));\\n\\n        assertThat(restored.getBagAttributeKeys().hasMoreElements()).isFalse();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void writesAndReadsEncodedBagAttributes() throws Exception {\\n        ASN1ObjectIdentifier friendlyName = new ASN1ObjectIdentifier(\\\"1.2.840.113549.1.9.20\\\");\\n        ASN1ObjectIdentifier localKeyId = new ASN1ObjectIdentifier(\\\"1.2.840.113549.1.9.21\\\");\\n        ASN1Integer friendlyNameValue = new ASN1Integer(BigInteger.valueOf(42L));\\n        ASN1Integer localKeyIdValue = new ASN1Integer(BigInteger.valueOf(7L));\\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl original = new PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl();\\n        original.setBagAttribute(friendlyName, friendlyNameValue);\\n        original.setBagAttribute(localKeyId, localKeyIdValue);\\n\\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl restored = readCarrier(writeCarrier(original));\\n\\n        assertThat(restored.getBagAttribute(friendlyName)).isEqualTo(friendlyNameValue);\\n        assertThat(restored.getBagAttribute(localKeyId)).isEqualTo(localKeyIdValue);\\n        assertThat(attributeKeys(restored)).containsExactly(friendlyName, localKeyId);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static byte[] writeCarrier(PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl carrier) throws Exception {\\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\\n            carrier.writeObject(output);\\n        }\\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\\n    }\\n\\n    private static PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl readCarrier(byte[] value) throws Exception {\\n        PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl carrier = new PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl();\\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(value))) {\\n            carrier.readObject(input);\\n        }\\n        return carrier;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static ASN1ObjectIdentifier[] attributeKeys(PKCS12BagAttributeCarrierImpl carrier) {\\n        ASN1ObjectIdentifier[] keys = new ASN1ObjectIdentifier[2];\\n        Enumeration<?> enumeration = carrier.getBagAttributeKeys();\\n        int index = 0;\\n        while (enumeration.hasMoreElements()) {\\n            keys[index] = (ASN1ObjectIdentifier) enumeration.nextElement();\\n            index++;\\n        }\\n        assertThat(index).isEqualTo(keys.length);\\n        return keys;\\n    }\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_37\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/X509UtilTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_37\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/X509UtilTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\\n\\nimport java.security.Provider;\\nimport java.security.Security;\\nimport java.util.Collections;\\n\\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.X509StoreCertCollection;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.x509.X509CollectionStoreParameters;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.x509.X509Store;\\nimport org.bouncycastle.x509.X509StoreSpi;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\npublic class X509UtilTest {\\n    private static final String STORE_ALGORITHM = \\\"CERTIFICATE/COLLECTION\\\";\\n    private static final String STORE_SPI_CLASS_NAME = X509StoreCertCollection.class.getName();\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void x509StoreLoadsBouncyCastleImplementationThroughProviderClassLoader() throws Exception {\\n        ensureStoreSpiIsReachable();\\n        Provider provider = new BouncyCastleProvider();\\n        X509CollectionStoreParameters parameters = new X509CollectionStoreParameters(Collections.emptyList());\\n\\n        X509Store store = X509Store.getInstance(STORE_ALGORITHM, parameters, provider);\\n\\n        assertThat(provider.get(\\\"X509Store.\\\" + STORE_ALGORITHM)).isEqualTo(STORE_SPI_CLASS_NAME);\\n        assertThat(store.getProvider()).isSameAs(provider);\\n        assertThat(store.getMatches(null)).isEmpty();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void x509StoreLoadsBouncyCastleImplementationThroughClassForNameForBootstrapProvider() throws Exception {\\n        ensureStoreSpiIsReachable();\\n        Provider bootstrapProvider = findBootstrapProvider();\\n        String propertyName = \\\"X509Store.\\\" + STORE_ALGORITHM;\\n        Object previousValue = bootstrapProvider.put(propertyName, STORE_SPI_CLASS_NAME);\\n        X509CollectionStoreParameters parameters = new X509CollectionStoreParameters(Collections.emptyList());\\n\\n        try {\\n            X509Store store = X509Store.getInstance(STORE_ALGORITHM, parameters, bootstrapProvider);\\n\\n            assertThat(store.getProvider()).isSameAs(bootstrapProvider);\\n            assertThat(store.getMatches(null)).isEmpty();\\n        } finally {\\n            if (previousValue == null) {\\n                bootstrapProvider.remove(propertyName);\\n            } else {\\n                bootstrapProvider.put(propertyName, previousValue);\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static void ensureStoreSpiIsReachable() {\\n        X509StoreSpi spi = new X509StoreCertCollection();\\n        assertThat(spi).isInstanceOf(X509StoreCertCollection.class);\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Provider findBootstrapProvider() {\\n        for (Provider provider : Security.getProviders()) {\\n            if (provider.getClass().getClassLoader() == null) {\\n                return provider;\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\\\"No bootstrap-loaded security provider is available\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n}\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/LocalizedMessageTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_38\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/LocalizedMessageTest.java\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\\n\\nimport java.util.ListResourceBundle;\\ni